Governor Wycliffe Oparanya has criticised the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission (EACC) for not cracking the whip on top Government officials involved in graft. Speaking in Butere yesterday, Mr Oparanya noted that those targeted in the graft war were mere mid-level officers while the influential and powerful individuals at the top were spared. ALSO READ:

